            <span id="Chapter_Title_Mod">
            Recent Family History
            </span>
            <span id="Contributor_Name_Mod">
            teresa roos
            </span>
            <span id="First_Paragraph_Mod">
            All my grandparents came to Arkansas because the railroad advertised acreage for cheap prices so people would build their businesses along the tracks. They sold the land to German Catholics for coal mining. The railroad said there was fruit growing etc. but there wasn't. <br /><br />
                
            Surnames on my father’s line are Layes and Besselman. Bauer and Fritchie were the surnames for his aunts and uncles.<br />
            </span>
            <!--div id="boxmodex3" class="clearfix">
                <div class="ChapterVideoDivMod">
