            <span id="First_Paragraph_Mod">My first memories were when I helped my Grandma (Clara Layes) feed the chickens. In the barn with the cow was a cornhusker machine. We would crack up the corn and then scatter it on the ground so the chickens could eat. I also hunted for eggs in the chicken house. There were two rows of nests. I gathered them sometimes. One part of the chicken house was for setting hens to hatch and raise for chickens. There was a big red rooster who would attack me. I would scream. My grandpa would get irritated at me for screaming. One July 4th I went to the mill with my dad and I was told to stay on the raised concrete foundation where it was safe. The rooster was there and attacked me. I screamed. My grandpa was irritated and my dad was mad and killed the rooster for dinner.

            <br />
            </span>
