            My dad was drafted to work as a civilian electrician in the steel mill in Kansas City around 1942. My mom’s brother Lawrence lived in Independence. He was either drafted or joined the navy. His wife Francis was pregnant and didn’t want to be alone, so she moved in with her sister. My mom and siblings moved up there and into their house. I didn't want to go to school in Missouri, so I stayed in Paris with my grandparents Joe and Julia Beshoner for the rest of first grade. Barbara and Rita (who were nicknamed Demp and Nuki) were still living at home. Demp had polio when she was five years old, and one leg was crippled.


            <br />
