                <span id="Second_Paragraph_Mod1" class="more">
                    We had catechism and Bible history at school. On Friday mornings we had Mass at church then we went over to the school. We didn’t have catechism on Fridays because of Mass. The 1st through 4th grade classes put on plays on a stage with a curtain. The 5th through 8th grade classes had a little library. There was an outdoor bathroom at the school and a girls and boys playground. We had a softball and baseball field. Once a baseball flew and hit me right in the chest. In 5th through 8th grade, we played games like Red Rover. We didn’t have any playground equipment. We also played house. John got into fights when he was in first and second grade. I remember coming in from recess and Clarine and I looked out at the playground and there was John and another kid fighting. There they were, rolling around on the ground, not paying any attention to the bell, and their shirt buttons were ripped off. Clarine and I had to sew them back on.  <br /><br />

                    I had Sister Irma in first grade. Sister Vivian also taught the lower grades. She was nice, but nicer to Clarine. Once, Clarine picked out a pink and green journal cover which I didn’t like. I said so, and the Sister Vivian said I should be nicer to my sister.  <br /><br />

