            <span id="First_Paragraph_Mod">
            For high school, I went to St. Scholastica, a Catholic boarding school in Fort Smith. I thought I was cool. I went home once a month. They gave me a test and didn’t do well, because in 8th grade, the district ran out of money and school ended in March. The teacher was then surprised I did well in biology because she expected me not to because she saw the scores on that test. We had PE and after-school volleyball, shuffleboard, and softball, but no competitive sports. Subiaco Academy boys had dances, a football team, and a homecoming queen from St. Scholastic or “Scho.” John and Ron went to Subiaco Academy or “Sube.” 
            <br />
            </span>
