            <span id="Second_Paragraph_Mod">
                I boarded freshman and sophomore years. One of the jobs around the dorms for the freshmen was to use a whisk broom to clean the steps. For my junior and senior years, I stayed with families and did babysitting and light housework. I was paid while also earning room and board. The first family I stayed with had three kids: Jackeline or Jackie, Dennis, and Damion. The parents were named Donhay and Harold Kellan. He called her, “Honey” so the kids called her “Honey” too. John Johnston was the father of the other family I stayed with. They had Sally, John and Julia. <br /><br />

                Clarine and I were in high school together for two years. I had cousins my age in my graduating class. Mary Jane and Teresa (Beshoner) Kern, Ritha Fay Brown—her mother was Pauline Koch, and Mary Beshoner. The convent slowed down high school and getting married.
            </span>
            <span id="See_More_Mod"><a href="#" id="restofstory4-show"  onclick="showHide('restofstory4');return false;">SEE MORE</a>
            </span>
